## County Results

The electoral landscape of [New Jersey](/New_Jersey) in 1992 presented a patchwork of allegiances, as depicted by the county-level voting patterns. Counties shaded in darker blue indicate a stronger preference for [Bill Clinton](/Bill_Clinton), with his support ranging from a solid 50-60% in certain areas to a still-winning 40-50% in others. Conversely, areas favoring [George H. W. Bush](/George_H._W._Bush) are marked in shades of red, illustrating his strongholds, particularly where he garnered 50-60% of the vote. Lighter red tones show counties where Bush secured 40-50% or 30-40%. These visual distinctions underscore the nuanced political leanings across the state, revealing where each candidate managed to consolidate their base and where the competition was more fiercely contested.

| President before election        | Elected President             |
| :------------------------------- | :---------------------------- |
| [George H. W. Bush](/George_H._W._Bush) | [Bill Clinton](/Bill_Clinton) |
